Something else to think about - you should all be working on your individual brand. You have no obligation to make content after this but some of you are going to use your tenure at EDHREC to get a bigger paycheck from another site. Share each other's articles on Twitter, interact with readers on our Facebook page. Make yourself seem accessible and your audience will grow. There are 26 days a month where you don't have an article out - spend 10 minutes every day building a following and your articles will get read more. Make statements in there that beg people to comment on wordpress the way they do on reddit

It isn't much work and you will get more Twitter followers which you may not care about, but Twitter followers are money. I bitch at brands on Twitter and when I passed 5k followers they started taking me way more seriously
Thank you Jason! For the recommendation and advice!

You guys are doing a good job writing, but commit to spending 5 or 10 minutes a day in 2019 to working on your brand. That's all it takes. Read each other's articles, comment on them, tweet them and engage with people on Twitter.  I am still learning it myself but that dumb "what card have you dealt the most damage with?" Tweet got me literally 20 new followers. See how DM Cross, Matt and a few other use Twitter

Our Facebook page has thousands of followers. The EDHREC Twitter account gained more followers in the time we have been doing articles than I got since 2011. EDHREC as a brand has reach, so use it. People who don't read the article every day still interact with the brand on other media platforms. People who won't read an article will take 2 seconds to answer a poll question on Facebook. Those people are coming to us daily, so interacting with EDHREC on Facebook and Twitter is 13 times as effective as only interacting when you publish an article. You guys get it. Anyway, I'm at my in-laws chugging red wine so I am rambling
